Ōkoro Māori Data Sovereignty Policy

Our Commitment

Ōkoro has been built upon the understanding that data is more than information. It represents people, whakapapa, relationships, knowledge, experiences, and connections with the natural world. We recognise that information relating to Māori carries cultural significance and should be treated with respect, care, and responsibility.

Our approach follows the principle that individuals retain authority over their own information while recognising the collective responsibilities that exist around mātauranga Māori and culturally significant knowledge.

Our Principles

Rangatiratanga — Authority

You remain in control of your personal information.

Ōkoro exists to support your understanding of environmental rhythms and personal wellbeing. Your information belongs to you. We do not claim ownership over the personal data you create while using Ōkoro.

You decide:

* what information you record
* what information you delete
* what information you export
* whether information is synchronised across your devices
* whether information is shared with other applications or services.

Whakapapa — Context Matters

Data does not exist in isolation.

Health information, maramataka observations, journals, environmental recordings, location information, and cultural preferences all carry context. We recognise these relationships and avoid using information outside the purpose for which it was provided.

Information is never separated from its intended meaning through unnecessary profiling or commercial exploitation.

Manaakitanga — Respect and Care

We collect only information that improves your experience.

Whenever possible:

* information is processed directly on your device
* personal journals remain private
* health information remains under your control
* location information is used only when required to calculate astronomical or environmental events.

We minimise data collection wherever practical.

Kaitiakitanga — Responsible Guardianship

Where information is entrusted to Ōkoro, we act as kaitiaki rather than owners.

Our responsibilities include:

* maintaining appropriate security
* protecting against unauthorised access
* ensuring reliable backups where cloud services are enabled
* allowing users to permanently remove their information
* maintaining transparency about how information is used.

Kotahitanga — Benefit

Data should create value for the person who generates it.

The primary purpose of collecting information within Ōkoro is to provide meaningful insights that help users reconnect with environmental cycles, improve wellbeing, and better understand relationships between celestial, seasonal, biological, and cultural rhythms.

We do not collect information solely to build advertising profiles or sell behavioural data.

Tikanga

Where Māori cultural knowledge is incorporated into Ōkoro, it is treated respectfully.

Traditional knowledge, language, names, and cultural practices are presented with acknowledgement that many traditions differ between iwi, hapū, whānau, and knowledge holders.

Ōkoro allows communities and individuals to maintain their own naming systems and cultural profiles rather than assuming there is only one authoritative tradition.

Artificial Intelligence

Artificial intelligence within Ōkoro is designed to assist—not replace—the knowledge and judgement of users.

AI-generated insights are based on information you choose to provide together with environmental data such as astronomical events, weather, seasonal patterns, and biological information where permission has been granted.

Your personal journals and health information are never used to train public artificial intelligence models without your explicit, informed consent.

Where possible, AI processing is performed using privacy-preserving methods and only for the purpose of delivering features you have requested.

Health Information

Where HealthKit or other health services are connected:

* you control which information is shared
* information is used only for the features you enable
* health data is never sold
* health information may be removed at any time without affecting ownership of your records.

If Premium features become unavailable, your underlying health records remain yours and remain accessible.

Your Rights

Every Ōkoro user has the right to:

* know what information is held
* export their information
* correct inaccurate information
* permanently delete their information
* disconnect third-party services
* choose whether information is stored locally or synchronised.

Community Knowledge

Some cultural datasets, including maramataka traditions, environmental observations, and naming systems, may be contributed by communities or individual knowledge holders.

Contributors retain recognition for their contributions where appropriate.

Ōkoro does not claim ownership over contributed mātauranga unless expressly transferred through written agreement.

Commercial Use

Ōkoro will never sell identifiable personal information.

Where anonymised statistical information is used to improve the application, it will be aggregated so individuals cannot reasonably be identified.

Any future research partnerships involving Māori data will require appropriate consultation, transparency, and consent.

Transparency

Whenever we collect, process, analyse, or share information, we aim to explain:

* what information is being used
* why it is needed
* how long it will be retained
* who can access it
* how you can remove it.

Our Commitment

Ōkoro exists to strengthen the relationship between people and the natural world.

Technology should empower rather than exploit.

We are committed to protecting the dignity, integrity, and sovereignty of the information entrusted to us, recognising that data carries both personal value and cultural significance.

As Ōkoro grows, this policy will continue to evolve in partnership with our users, Māori communities, and emerging best practice in Indigenous Data Sovereignty.
